1
00:00:03,294 --> 00:00:05,922
[mellow piano music]

2
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:09,718
- This place
looks incredible, Logan.

3
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:14,764
- Okay, don't hate me, but...

4
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:17,225
But I need to reschedule
our trip this weekend.

5
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:19,602
- I already took off work
on Friday.

6
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:21,146
- I'm sorry.

7
00:00:21,229 --> 00:00:22,772
I just got invited

8
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:24,983
to speak at an immigrant rights
rally on Saturday.

9
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:27,444
- Next weekend,
we have dinner at the Rubins.

10
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,612
We can't cancel that.

11
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:34,242
- Well, I know we shouldn't,
but what if we did?

12
00:00:34,325 --> 00:00:36,661
Cancelling's all the rage
these days.

13
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:39,748
- Oh, love in the time
of cancel culture?

14
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:43,418
- I'm just saying that anything
or anyone can be cancelled.

15
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:45,462
[glass shatters]
- [gasps]

16
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:47,130
- Stay there.

17
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:50,133
[ominous music]

18
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:52,010
♪ ♪

19
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:53,970
It's a brick.
You okay?

20
00:00:54,053 --> 00:00:57,098
- We can't live like this.
- Call 911.

21
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,518
- Wait, where are you going?

22
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:02,520
- I'm just gonna talk to them.

23
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:08,860
♪ ♪

24
00:01:08,943 --> 00:01:10,695
- Logan, don't!

25
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,656
- [grunts]

26
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:17,535
- [gasps, screams]

27
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:20,663
[sobbing]

28
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:25,376
[tense music]

29
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,628
♪ ♪

30
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:28,171
- Yeah, tonight's
a little gallery actually.

31
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:30,340
- Thanks a lot.
- Can I help you, sir?

32
00:01:30,423 --> 00:01:32,050
- Tiff, you want
anything to eat?

33
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:35,345
Sandwich, chips?
- No, the soda's fine, thanks.

34
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:38,348
[soft music playing]

35
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:39,891
♪ ♪

36
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:43,353
- Tiffany Wallace?

37
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:45,355
- Jemila.
[chuckles]

38
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,357
It's been a long time.
It's good to see your face.

39
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,567
- I thought you moved away.

40
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,861
- I did, but I'm back.

41
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:56,699
- You still a cop?
- FBI.

42
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,326
This is actually
my partner Stuart.

43
00:01:58,409 --> 00:02:00,328
- Hey.
- Stuart, this is Jemila.

44
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:01,996
We grew up together
in Bed-Stuy.

45
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,040
- We used to be friends...

46
00:02:04,123 --> 00:02:06,459
till she put my brother away
for ten years.

47
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:08,545
- He was dealing
to high school kids.

48
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:09,879
I was doing my job.

49
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:11,881
- Hm, that's the problem
right there.

50
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,967
You got the wrong job.

51
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:18,137
[soft dramatic music]

52
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:21,391
♪ ♪

53
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:22,725
- You good?

54
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:25,061
- Yeah,
comes with the territory.

55
00:02:25,144 --> 00:02:28,481
[cell phone rings]

56
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:30,984
- We gotta go.

57
00:02:33,152 --> 00:02:35,572
- 15 minutes ago,
Congressman Logan Reed

58
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:40,076
was shot and killed
at his home in Scarsdale.

59
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,744
Now, as most of you know,
Logan Reed

60
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:43,746
was a rising star
in the Democratic Party,

61
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,039
a former prosecutor.

62
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:46,791
He rose to national prominence
last summer

63
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,877
during all of
the racial unrest.

64
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,129
Love him or hate him,
he was one of the most

65
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:53,423
talked about politicians
in the country.

66
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,550
- The story just broke online,
so the entire country's

67
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:58,219
about to start asking if this
was politically motivated.

68
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,596
We need answers and fast.

69
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,264
- Let's get some, people.
Go to work.

70
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:02,557
Now, Reed's
biggest campaign issues

71
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,933
were racial justice
and police reform.

72
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:05,768
He had a lot
of impassioned enemies,

73
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,770
which means these days
a nonstop supply

74
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:08,897
of death threats and hate mail,

75
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,565
so let's scour
through all of it.

76
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:11,983
Let's flag
everything high risk

77
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:13,234
and ID any suspects

78
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:16,237
within a striking distance
of the city, yep?

79
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:17,739
- Anything from
the crime scene yet?

80
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:19,198
- Maggie and OA just got there.

81
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:20,825
Scola and Tiffany
are minutes away.

82
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,619
- All right,
regular updates on all fronts.

83
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,454
This story
is going to move and fast.

84
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:25,914
We have to stay
one step ahead of it.

85
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:27,790
- Yes, ma'am.

86
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,959
- [sighs]

87
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:32,462
- I'll have to arrange you
at about 60 feet.

88
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:35,840
[police radio chatter]

89
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:38,134
[person shouting indistinctly]

90
00:03:38,217 --> 00:03:40,136
- What do we know so far?
- Not enough.

91
00:03:40,219 --> 00:03:41,721
All these neighbors,
not one eyewitness.

92
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:42,931
- And no security cameras
in the suburbs,

93
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:44,349
so we're flying blind out here.

94
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:45,808
- In a neighborhood like this,
there's gotta be

95
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:46,851
doorbell cameras
in every house.

96
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:49,145
- True,
but the Reeds' is broken,

97
00:03:49,228 --> 00:03:50,647
and there's no hits
on the neighbors' yet.

98
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,649
Scarsdale PD's
still canvassing.

99
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:53,983
- Reed was having dinner
with his wife

100
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,193
when someone threw
a garden brick

101
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,235
through the side window.

102
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,488
He was shot the second
he opened the front door.

103
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,114
- We're gonna go speak
with his wife now.

104
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,491
- We'll take a look
at the window.

105
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:02,992
- Meet back here in ten.

106
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,661
♪ ♪

107
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:05,954
- Yep, close it up.

108
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:07,705
- Out of camera range,

109
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:09,624
trees and bushes
providing cover.

110
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:11,209
- Yeah, the killer was smart.

111
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:13,169
Could have waited hours
for the perfect moment.

112
00:04:13,252 --> 00:04:15,171
- Yeah, copy that.

113
00:04:15,254 --> 00:04:17,507
- Canvass just turned up
a witness one block over.

114
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,467
Lady getting her mail
saw a stranger

115
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:21,469
come out of a backyard
wearing a black hoodie.

116
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:23,513
- Where was that?
- Six houses that way.

117
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:26,182
- She give a description?
- Just the hoodie.

118
00:04:26,265 --> 00:04:27,475
- Got it, thanks.

119
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,478
So the shooter
disguised his identity

120
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:31,854
and avoided cameras
by moving

121
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,231
through backyards.

122
00:04:35,274 --> 00:04:37,068
- We got lots
of death threats,

123
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:40,863
but I never thought
it would actually happen.

124
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,700
It was just background noise.

125
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:45,660
- Any of those threats
stick out?

126
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:47,286
Anything seem like
an escalation?

127
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:54,335
- It's okay.
I know this must be hard.

128
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:55,878
You can take your time.

129
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,006
- It's not that.
It's just...

130
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:01,592
One thing does stand out,
but I don't...

131
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:05,596
I don't want to give
the wrong impression.

132
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:10,059
- You can't say
the wrong thing here.

133
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:13,354
- There was a protest
at our house last week

134
00:05:13,438 --> 00:05:17,233
that got loud and scary.

135
00:05:17,316 --> 00:05:19,110
They broke our doorbell camera,

136
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:20,737
and then someone threw
a brick through the window

137
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,405
just like tonight.

138
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:23,865
- Did you see
who threw the brick

139
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,450
or get any pictures
of the protestors?

140
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,785
- No, Logan wouldn't
let me outside.

141
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:28,911
It was just...

142
00:05:30,496 --> 00:05:31,622
A little surprising.

143
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,542
- Surprising how?

144
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:37,462
- As you know, Logan...

145
00:05:37,545 --> 00:05:39,505
was a champion
for racial equality.

146
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:43,926
But this crowd
was mostly Black.

147
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:46,971
I know.

148
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,432
I sound terrible
even saying it.

149
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:51,601
- Did you call the police?

150
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:52,727
- I wanted to, but he said

151
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:55,313
it would only
inflame the situation.

152
00:05:55,396 --> 00:05:58,566
♪ ♪

153
00:05:58,649 --> 00:06:00,151
- All right, folks,
here's the question--

154
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:03,321
how did a progressive ally
like Logan Reed

155
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:06,699
end up in the crosshairs
of a minority protest group?

156
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:08,409
- Well, the protest
at Reed's house

157
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,453
was organized by Damian Thomas,

158
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:12,789
a community activist
who lives in Reed's district,

159
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,582
but he despises him.

160
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:16,626
Called him
"the worst kind of racist,

161
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:17,794
"a white liberal hypocrite

162
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:19,587
"who co-opted
the Civil Rights Movement

163
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:22,256
for his personal gain."
- That's pretty harsh.

164
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:24,425
Next question is
why did Thomas feel this way?

165
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:25,593
- Well, before he ran
for Congress,

166
00:06:25,676 --> 00:06:28,471
Reed was a prosecutor
known for being tough on crime.

167
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,098
- Right, so Thomas thought
he was a hypocrite.

168
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:31,974
One minute, he's putting
young Black men in prison,

169
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:33,643
the next,
he's out on the streets

170
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,311
protesting
with Black activists.

171
00:06:35,394 --> 00:06:37,021
- And he was preaching
all his newfound wokeness

172
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,107
from his big-ass pad
in the suburbs.

173
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,483
- And that.

174
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,527
But would Thomas Reed
really kill over all this?

175
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:45,488
- According
to Thomas himself, yes.

176
00:06:45,571 --> 00:06:48,991
- Logan Reed is a hypocrite
and a predator

177
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,910
who needs to disappear.
- Hey.

178
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:52,620
Punch into
his waistband there.

179
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:54,163
- You can't play
both sides, Reed!

180
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,289
[people chanting]
Reed must go!

181
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,667
Reed must go!
Reed must go!

182
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,502
- Looks like a .38.

183
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:00,962
- Same caliber
used to kill Reed.

184
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:02,505
I want to locate this guy now.

185
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,799
- Okay, he's got
an apartment in Bushwick

186
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:06,676
and a nonprofit office
in Crown Heights.

187
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,219
- Okay, coordinate
with Maggie and OA.

188
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:09,679
I want a team
in both locations.

189
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,972
- Actually, Jubal...
- Yeah?

190
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:12,890
- Social media says
Thomas is hosting a rally

191
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:14,392
this morning
outside City Hall Park.

192
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:16,727
He should be there for
at least another half an hour.

193
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:19,313
- Okay, do that.
- Jubal.

194
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:21,149
Guys, quick thought.

195
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:22,150
- Homeland Security
have something?

196
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,359
- Unofficially, yes.

197
00:07:23,442 --> 00:07:25,194
We've got Thomas
on a watchlist.

198
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:27,363
You want his email, text,
and call history,

199
00:07:27,446 --> 00:07:29,031
it's yours
provided your data source

200
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,324
stays off of any reports.

201
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:33,870
- What did he do to get himself
on an unofficial watchlist?

202
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,788
- He was arrested
three times last summer

203
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:37,540
during the police reform
demonstrations.

204
00:07:37,623 --> 00:07:40,626
- Violent offenses?
- Curfew violations.

205
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:43,212
- Curfew violations?

206
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:46,424
So he stayed out
past his bedtime

207
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:47,884
and ended up
on a damn watchlist,

208
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,385
is that it?

209
00:07:49,468 --> 00:07:52,722
- Uh, this type of surveillance
is standard procedure.

210
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,348
- Yeah,
that's part of the problem.

211
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:55,558
- Yeah, look,
if there's any question

212
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,185
about the legality
of the intel,

213
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,895
we'll just build our case
another way.

214
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:01,439
This investigation's
just too important.

215
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:05,193
- Yeah, agreed,
let's not take any chances.

216
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:06,611
Let's bring him in, yeah?

217
00:08:06,694 --> 00:08:13,743
♪ ♪

218
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:16,787
- You know...

219
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:19,165
It's one thing to wonder
if the government

220
00:08:19,248 --> 00:08:22,251
is spying on minority groups
they think are threatening.

221
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:25,087
It's another thing
to know that they do.

222
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:26,464
And then to work
with the people that do it,

223
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:29,133
it makes me feel like
a damn hypocrite,

224
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,594
like I'm fighting
the wrong fight.

225
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:32,678
- Yeah.

226
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:35,473
Hard to thread the needle
between where you work

227
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:37,475
and who you really are...

228
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:42,939
Especially these days.

229
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:45,775
♪ ♪

230
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:48,653
- Yeah, that's why
I stopped trying.

231
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:52,448
[people chanting]
Police reform now!

232
00:08:52,531 --> 00:08:53,616
- That's him.
- All right.

233
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:56,118
Let's get into place.
We'll grab him when he's done.

234
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:58,329
- Black men
in this city make up

235
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:02,583
a quarter of the population
and half of all arrests.

236
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,335
That's not okay!

237
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:07,004
Not if we're serious
about equality.

238
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:09,715
That's why we're here today!

239
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,343
That's why we're marching
on Saturday!

240
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:15,346
[people chanting]
Police reform now!

241
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:20,017
- I want to thank you all
for coming out.

242
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:23,354
I'll see you on Saturday--
Bryant Park at noon!

243
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:26,482
[cheers and applause]

244
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:32,863
- Damian Thomas.

245
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,157
- This is a peaceful gathering.
We have every right to be here.

246
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,159
- FBI, we're gonna need you
to come with us.

247
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:40,121
- Regarding what?
- The murder of Logan Reed.

248
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:42,164
- That's ridiculous.

249
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,332
- Turn around, put your hands
behind your back.

250
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,250
- Maybe slapping on the cuffs
isn't the play right now.

251
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,836
- Riding behind me,
he's wearing cuffs.

252
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,254
- Let's just get him
to the car.

253
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:49,463
- No, no,
get your hands off me!

254
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:50,214
- That's it.

255
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:51,299
Put your hands
behind your back.

256
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,676
- Laila, bring the camera!

257
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,927
- Dad, what the hell
is going on?

258
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:57,013
- You need to back up, ma'am.
- Why are you arresting him?

259
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:57,930
- We're not.

260
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,181
We're just detaining him
for questioning.

261
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:00,516
- Why are you arresting
my father?

262
00:10:00,599 --> 00:10:01,642
- Stand back now.

263
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:02,810
- Why are you arresting
my father?

264
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:04,854
- FBI, back up!
- You kidding me?

265
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:05,855
You won't even
look me in the eye?

266
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:07,398
- I'm looking right at you,

267
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:09,025
and I'm telling you
to back down.

268
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:12,695
- I hope it feels good, Sister,
selling out your people.

269
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:14,196
- He didn't do nothing!

270
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,074
- You don't know me.

271
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,701
- Y'all crazy!
- Bullies!

272
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:21,704
[people shouting indistinctly]

273
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:25,041
♪ ♪

274
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:28,002
- You think
I killed Logan Reed?

275
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:30,755
- You stood outside his house
last week with a gun

276
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:32,340
yelling that he needed
to disappear,

277
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:34,675
so yeah.

278
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,677
- I admit I got carried away
with that,

279
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,597
but I didn't mean what I said.
I don't even own a gun.

280
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,724
- All right,
let's try this again.

281
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:44,560
Maybe this time
don't treat us like idiots.

282
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,562
- [chuckles]
Come on, man.

283
00:10:46,645 --> 00:10:49,231
I took that gun
off a kid at the rally.

284
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:52,526
He was a hothead.
I don't stand for violence.

285
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,195
- Except for when
you're making death threats.

286
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:55,321
- Or someone throws a brick

287
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:56,530
through the congressman's
window.

288
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,074
- The hothead did that.

289
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,575
It's a good thing
I took away his gun.

290
00:10:59,658 --> 00:11:00,951
- You give it back to him?

291
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:02,787
- I got rid of it
at a gun buyback.

292
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,538
I got the receipt, if it helps.

293
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,666
- Where were you at 7:00 p.m.
last night?

294
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:12,588
- I know y'all got a job to do,

295
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:15,257
but this story gets old.

296
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:17,593
Rich white guy gets shot.

297
00:11:17,676 --> 00:11:21,514
Cops go nuts, start rounding up
innocent Black men.

298
00:11:21,597 --> 00:11:23,391
The FBI gets involved.
- Okay.

299
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:25,726
A United States congressman
was murdered.

300
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,728
This country
is at a tipping point.

301
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:29,980
- And yet five miles away
in his own district,

302
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:32,483
the murders of young, Black men
barely register,

303
00:11:32,566 --> 00:11:34,610
so forgive me if
I'm not shedding any tears

304
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:36,737
for this two-faced politician.

305
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:40,574
♪ ♪

306
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:42,451
- Where were you at 7:00 p.m.?

307
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:47,039
- Making sure my people are
fairly treated by the police.

308
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:50,626
I was speaking
at a community action dinner.

309
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:52,461
That's what I do.

310
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,630
In fact, when you arrested me,
I was on my way

311
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,007
to visit the mother
of a young, Black man

312
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:59,927
who had been murdered
for no damned reason.

313
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:02,638
This kid's
minding his own business.

314
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:05,141
A brick gets thrown
through his window.

315
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,935
He rushes outside,
gets shot twice.

316
00:12:08,018 --> 00:12:10,146
- When was that exactly?

317
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,772
- Last night.

318
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:13,315
- Do you know
the victim's name?

319
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:16,861
- Of course I do--
Marcus Ervin.

320
00:12:20,698 --> 00:12:22,199
- Thomas' alibi checks out.

321
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:23,701
Security footage
from the restaurant

322
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,995
confirms that he was having
dinner when Reed was shot.

323
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:28,456
- NYPD says Marcus Ervin
was shot last night

324
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,374
in Brooklyn around 10:00 p.m.
while he was standing

325
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:32,042
in the doorway
of his ground floor apartment

326
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:33,961
after a rock came crashing
through his window.

327
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:36,005
- Same MO as Reed.

328
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:38,549
- They run the ballistics yet?
- It's the same gun.

329
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:40,801
- All right, that's two murders
within three hours.

330
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:42,011
- That we know of.

331
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:43,846
We could be looking
at a killing spree.

332
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:45,514
All right, go to Brooklyn now.

333
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:48,350
[dramatic music]

334
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:48,767
- [sighs]

335
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:55,024
- Game faces, people!

336
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:57,359
We now have two victims
of the same gunman

337
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:58,694
who might not be done
shooting yet.

338
00:12:58,777 --> 00:12:59,904
Three hours after killing

339
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:01,906
Congressman Reed
in the suburbs,

340
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,324
our shooter resurfaced
in Brooklyn

341
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:05,034
and killed this man,
Marcus Ervin.

342
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:06,911
He's 20 years old.
He's a retail clerk.

343
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:09,497
Lived with his mother,
was taking IT classes at night.

344
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:11,540
The question is why--
either there's a connection

345
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,167
between these two murders,

346
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,877
or we have a madman
on the loose

347
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,878
throwing rocks
through random windows

348
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,421
and shooting whoever walks out.

349
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,756
- If these two men
were targeted,

350
00:13:18,839 --> 00:13:20,049
they were not killed
for their differences.

351
00:13:20,132 --> 00:13:21,717
They were killed
for their similarities.

352
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,511
What do these two men
have in common?

353
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:25,054
- There's no luck
on the political front.

354
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:26,388
I just talked
to Reed's chief of staff.

355
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:27,765
She doesn't know Marcus,
but she put his name

356
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:29,350
in the volunteer database,
and there's no record

357
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:31,435
that he ever worked there.
- Same goes for Reed's wife.

358
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,229
I mean, as far as she knows,
Reed never spent

359
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:34,396
any time
in that part of Bushwick.

360
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,898
- Okay, thanks, guys.

361
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,149
Hey, Kelly, have your team
start scrubbing

362
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,235
through videos from the area
surrounding both crime scenes

363
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:40,402
and flag anything
that appears in both.

364
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:41,403
- On it.

365
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,405
- Ian, you guys run financials
on both victims.

366
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,241
Look for any common patterns--
expenses, accounts.

367
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:46,784
Let's get creative, folks!

368
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,577
Our shooter might have plans
to strike again.

369
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,329
Travel history,
online hangouts,

370
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,580
common acquaintances.

371
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,873
I don't know.
Surprise me.

372
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:53,916
- You got anything
from Tiffany and Scola yet?

373
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,460
- They're talking
to Marcus' mother as we speak.

374
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:59,463
Maybe she knows something
we haven't seen from here.

375
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:02,466
[soft dramatic music]

376
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,801
- You're telling me
the same guy

377
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:06,095
who killed a congressman
killed my son?

378
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:08,389
- That's our working theory
at the moment.

379
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:11,058
- So that's why y'all suddenly
give a damn--

380
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:13,060
'cause a white congressman
is involved.

381
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:14,937
- Ma'am, we're just trying
to find the man

382
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,564
who shot your son.

383
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:19,608
Can you think of anything
that might connect Marcus

384
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:21,277
to Logan Reed?
- No.

385
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:24,071
Marcus wasn't involved
in politics.

386
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:25,573
- Have there been
recent threats,

387
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:27,950
or did he have any enemies?
- Yeah.

388
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,286
You're not gonna like it.

389
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:33,581
He was a good kid.
Kept his head down.

390
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:36,959
Did his work,
and I can tell you right now

391
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:40,087
he wanted nothing
to do with the gangs.

392
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:44,174
Only people who hated my son
were the local cops.

393
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:46,093
- Excuse me?

394
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:47,970
- Marcus didn't like
the way the police

395
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:52,099
treated people around here,
so if they crossed the line,

396
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:54,143
he'd let 'em hear it,

397
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:57,813
and they crossed
plenty of lines.

398
00:14:57,896 --> 00:14:59,315
My opinion?

399
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:03,861
Cops killed my son.

400
00:15:03,944 --> 00:15:06,363
- And do you have any evidence
to back that up?

401
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:12,036
♪ ♪

402
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:14,288
- Two days ago,
some off-duty cop

403
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:16,790
jumped out
of an unmarked cop car

404
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:19,001
and beat him senseless.

405
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:21,837
♪ ♪

406
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:24,006
- And did Marcus
go to the hospital?

407
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:26,008
- He was too afraid.

408
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:30,179
Cops said to keep
his mouth shut.

409
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,014
- Did you take photos
of the injuries?

410
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:34,350
♪ ♪

411
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,518
If you can tell us
where the attack took place,

412
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:39,021
we'll talk to the NYPD
and get you some answers.

413
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,439
- [scoffs]

414
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:43,108
I won't hold my breath.

415
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:45,903
♪ ♪

416
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:49,615
- We're gonna find the person
responsible for Marcus' death,

417
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:50,991
so please,

418
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:53,827
can you tell us exactly
where Marcus was attacked?

419
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:57,206
♪ ♪

420
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:59,541
- The intersection of Irving
and Dekalb in Bushwick.

421
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,543
We have video of the attack.
- Oh, great.

422
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,379
- Happened
at 4:17 p.m. Tuesday.

423
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:06,006
- All right, eyes up, people!
Let's check it out.

424
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:09,051
- That is Marcus Ervin
stepping off the curb,

425
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:12,763
and I presume that is the cop
his mother was talking about.

426
00:16:12,846 --> 00:16:14,348
- He could have killed him
right here.

427
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:15,724
Why wait a few days?
- Mm.

428
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,226
Are we gonna be able
to identify the attacker?

429
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:18,894
- No, it's too grainy
for an ID,

430
00:16:18,977 --> 00:16:21,105
but we can read
the license plate.

431
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,399
- Yep, got it.
Car is owned by a Cody McCowan.

432
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,859
He lives in Flatbush.
- He with the NYPD?

433
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,611
- No, definitely not.

434
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,239
- But Marcus' mom
said a cop beat him up.

435
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:31,740
- Well, his mother was wrong.

436
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,033
McCowan has got three priors,

437
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,411
all for assault,
no convictions.

438
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,914
He's got an outstanding warrant
for aggravated battery.

439
00:16:38,997 --> 00:16:41,542
- Hate Crimes has
a pretty big file on this guy.

440
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,293
He used to own
a sporting goods shop.

441
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:44,420
Went out of business,

442
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,171
channeled his anger
into politics,

443
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,423
started a local group

444
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:50,342
called the Brooklyn Blockade--
BKB--

445
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:53,095
fighting neighborhood change
with intimidation and violence.

446
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,179
- Neighborhood change,

447
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:56,223
meaning he wants
to keep his neighborhood white.

448
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:58,100
But why attack Marcus?
Why'd he hate him so much?

449
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,269
- I'm not sure yet.
- There's gotta be a reason.

450
00:17:00,352 --> 00:17:01,645
Let's find it.
- Hey.

451
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:03,272
I just found a connection.

452
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:05,774
Looks like Cody hated
Congressman Reed too.

453
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:07,484
- What?
What are you talking about?

454
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,111
- He made a bunch of
online threats against him

455
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,279
over the past few months.

456
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:13,907
He blamed politicians like Reed
for ruining his community.

457
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,535
- Hey, McCowan's got six guns
registered to his name.

458
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:19,204
- One of 'em a .38?
- Smith & Wesson 640.

459
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:21,582
- All right, folks, we got
a new leader in the clubhouse!

460
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:23,959
Cody McCowan,
he assaulted Marcus Ervin,

461
00:17:24,042 --> 00:17:25,502
he threatened Congressman Reed,

462
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:27,921
and he has a gun
that matches the murder weapon.

463
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,631
Let's get an address
and bring him in.

464
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:33,177
♪ ♪

465
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:36,847
- Cody McCowan on any
of your unofficial watchlists?

466
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:39,641
- No.
- Come on.

467
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:42,519
What's a white boy gotta do
to get some love from the DHS?

468
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:45,439
- [sighs]
Look, I don't make the lists.

469
00:17:45,522 --> 00:17:47,858
- That is a weak excuse.

470
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:50,027
- Just telling you
the way it is.

471
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,987
- Yeah, well,
the way it is sucks.

472
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:54,031
- You got a problem
with the rules,

473
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:55,991
take it up
the chain of command.

474
00:17:56,074 --> 00:17:58,619
- Y'all have been hiding
behind that line for 100 years.

475
00:17:58,702 --> 00:18:00,496
- I don't appreciate
your attitude.

476
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:01,997
- My attitude?
What does that mean?

477
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,290
- What the hell
are you trying--

478
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,000
- Okay, enough, enough.
We got work to do.

479
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:10,339
♪ ♪

480
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:12,007
- I got an address.
- Yeah?

481
00:18:12,090 --> 00:18:13,675
- Hate Crimes says
McCowan and the BKB

482
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:16,512
hang out at a place
called Irish Haven in Brooklyn.

483
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:17,679
Bar's owned
by Cody's mother Janine.

484
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:18,931
- Okay, great,
call Maggie and OA.

485
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:20,682
Get 'em over there now.

486
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:25,896
♪ ♪

487
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:27,272
Tiffany.

488
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:35,030
So I get it.

489
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:38,575
You disagree
with what DHS is doing,

490
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:41,829
but you were
out of line back there.

491
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:43,247
- Excuse me?

492
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,499
- Look, this place, the JOC,

493
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:48,210
it only works if we're a team,
you know?

494
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:51,547
If we play together in harmony.

495
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:56,218
End of the day,
we got a job to do.

496
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:58,846
It's simple as that.

497
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,559
Thanks.

498
00:19:08,146 --> 00:19:09,898
- Can I get another one,
please?

499
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:12,609
And this time, try to make sure
this one's not so bubbly.

500
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:15,195
- Can I help you?
- Cody McCowan, you know him?

501
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:16,530
- Sorry, man.

502
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:17,948
Cool vest, though.

503
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:20,909
Those thing come with a helmet?
- [chuckles]

504
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,411
- I'ma need you
to think really hard

505
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,121
before you
open your mouth again.

506
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:26,582
Cody McCowan,
